    'history.tag': 'Department history',
    'history.title': 'From the origins to <em>the present day</em>',
    'history.h1Title': 'Beginnings',
    'history.h1Text': 'Training of engineering staff for the sugar industry is linked to the founding of the Kyiv Polytechnic Institute in 1884. The first lectures on fermentation technology were given by K.G. Schindler.',
    'history.h2Title': 'Department founded',
    'history.h2Text': 'In 1930 the Kyiv Institute of Sugar Industry was established on the basis of KPI, and later the Kyiv Technological Institute of Food Industry (KTIFP). The department was headed by Oleksandr Lazarevych Malikov — one of the founders of the scientific foundations of fermentation in Ukraine.',
    'history.h3Title': 'Science development',
    'history.h3Text': 'The Department of Fermentation and Winemaking Technology was headed by Professor A.A. Feldman. In 1940 he defended his thesis and published the fundamental monograph «Chemistry and Technology of Vodka».',
    'history.h4Title': 'New era',
    'history.h4Text': 'From 1968 to 1991 the department was headed by the distinguished scientist Prof. P.S. Tsyhankov. Under his leadership the department saw strong development of its scientific and staff potential.',
    'history.h5Title': 'Professor V.A. Domaretskyi',
    'history.h5Text': 'From 1991 to 2016 the department was headed by Honoured Scientist of Ukraine Prof. V.A. Domaretskyi. Under his leadership the department developed innovative technologies and over 30 dissertations were defended.',
    'history.h6Title': 'Present day',
    'history.h6Text': 'Since 2016 the department has been headed by Assoc. Prof. A.M. Kuts. The department is developing dynamically, introducing dual education, international exchange programmes and innovative technologies into the curriculum. Over 20 articles are published annually in Scopus and Web of Science.',
